  "notes": [
    "Students majoring in a different program of study may find that a minor in philosophy is an invaluable addition to their educational plan. Prospective transfer students interested in minoring in philosophy are encouraged to complete two lower-division philosophy courses, or their articulated equivalents, prior to transferring: PHIL 9 \u2013 Introductory Symbolic Logic One additional lower-division philosophy course Refer to the \u201cPreparation for the Minor\u201d section below for courses approved to apply to each of the requirements listed above. Students who cannot enroll in the articulated equivalent of PHIL 9 at a California Community College are strongly encouraged to take PHIL 9 at UC Santa Cruz before their first fall quarter. PHIL 9 is offered online during a 10-week summer session. For more information, please visit the UC Santa Cruz Summer Edge webpage . Please visit the Philosophy website to learn more about this major.",
    "UC Santa Cruz students may choose to complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and allowable credits. While a minor will appear on a student's official transcript, it will not be listed on their diploma. Pursuing a minor is a personal decision that should align with a student's educational and career goals. Students do not apply for minors when submitting their application to UC Santa Cruz. After enrolling, transfer students interested in pursuing a minor should contact the department offering the minor for guidance."
